comments.body:
There is extra whitespace, otherwise it's ok.

{noformat}
node [-list [-states <States>| -showDetails | -all] | -status <NodeId>]
{noformat}

should be:
{noformat}
node [-list [-states <States>|-showDetails|-all] |-status <NodeId>]
{noformat}

[~ajithshetty]

Than for the patch. Few nits
- In below code,
{noformat}
	    pw.println(
	        "usage: node [-list [-states <States>|-showDetails|-all] |-status <NodeId>]");
{noformat}
Suboptions of {{node -list}} could be displayed in alphabetical order with *-all* at start (currently all options in help are displayed in alphabetical)
- I am not sure whether to show *-help*  also there. Clearly we are showing -help below. There are no strong arguments for that, but more thoughts are welcome.
